# RDS security & RDS Proxy

## Security ‚Äî four layers

- **Network** ‚Äî private subnets; SG allows the DB port **from the app SG only** (never public)
- **At rest** ‚Äî KMS AES-256, **enabled at creation** (else snapshot‚Üícopy-encrypted‚Üírestore)
- **In transit** ‚Äî SSL/TLS via parameter group + regional CA
- **IAM DB auth** ‚Äî short-lived token, no stored password

## RDS Proxy ‚Äî the connection pool

DBs cap connections; **Lambda opens one per invocation** ‚Üí exhausts the DB. RDS Proxy multiplexes **thousands of app connections ‚Üí a small backend pool**.

- **Handles failover** ‚Äî reconnects in seconds, app's link stays open
- **IAM + Secrets Manager** creds
- The standard part of any **Lambda + relational** stack
